247 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
248 // Snippets ----
249 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
250 ----
251 // When spilling a virtual register, we also spill any snippets it is connected ----
252 // to. The snippets are small live ranges that only have a single real use, ----
253 // leftovers from live range splitting. Spilling them enables memory operand ----
254 // folding or tightens the live range around the single use. ----
255 // ----
256 // This minimizes register pressure and maximizes the store-to-load distance for ----
257 // spill slots which can be important in tight loops. ----
258 ----
259 /// If MI is a COPY to or from Reg, return the other register, otherwise return ----
260 /// 0. ----
261 static Register isCopyOf(const MachineInstr &MI, Register Reg) { 0
262 assert(!MI.isBundled()); 0
263 if (!MI.isCopy()) 0
264 return Register(); 0
265 ----
266 const MachineOperand &DstOp = MI.getOperand(0); 0
267 const MachineOperand &SrcOp = MI.getOperand(1); 0
268 ----
269 // TODO: Probably only worth allowing subreg copies with undef dests. ----
270 if (DstOp.getSubReg() != SrcOp.getSubReg()) 0
271 return Register(); 0
272 if (DstOp.getReg() == Reg) 0
273 return SrcOp.getReg(); 0
274 if (SrcOp.getReg() == Reg) 0
275 return DstOp.getReg(); 0
276 return Register(); 0
277 } ----
278 ----
279 /// Check for a copy bundle as formed by SplitKit. ----
280 static Register isCopyOfBundle(const MachineInstr &FirstMI, Register Reg) { 0
281 if (!FirstMI.isBundled()) 0
282 return isCopyOf(FirstMI, Reg); 0
283 ----
284 assert(!FirstMI.isBundledWithPred() && FirstMI.isBundledWithSucc() && 0
285 "expected to see first instruction in bundle"); ----
286 ----
287 Register SnipReg; 0
288 MachineBasicBlock::const_instr_iterator I = FirstMI.getIterator(); 0
289 while (I->isBundledWithSucc()) { 0
290 const MachineInstr &MI = *I; 0
291 if (!MI.isCopy()) 0
292 return Register(); 0
293 ----
294 const MachineOperand &DstOp = MI.getOperand(0); 0
295 const MachineOperand &SrcOp = MI.getOperand(1); 0
296 if (DstOp.getReg() == Reg) { 0
297 if (!SnipReg) 0
298 SnipReg = SrcOp.getReg(); 0
299 else if (SnipReg != SrcOp.getReg()) 0
300 return Register(); 0
301 } else if (SrcOp.getReg() == Reg) { 0
302 if (!SnipReg) 0
303 SnipReg = DstOp.getReg(); 0
304 else if (SnipReg != DstOp.getReg()) 0
305 return Register(); 0
306 } ----
307 ----
308 ++I; 0
309 } ----
310 ----
311 return Register(); 0
312 } ----

314 static void getVDefInterval(const MachineInstr &MI, LiveIntervals &LIS) { 0
315 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_defs()) 0
316 if (MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
317 LIS.getInterval(MO.getReg()); 0
318 } 0
319 ----
320 /// isSnippet - Identify if a live interval is a snippet that should be spilled. ----
321 /// It is assumed that SnipLI is a virtual register with the same original as ----
322 /// Edit->getReg(). ----
323 bool InlineSpiller::isSnippet(const LiveInterval &SnipLI) { 0
324 Register Reg = Edit->getReg(); 0
325 ----
326 // A snippet is a tiny live range with only a single instruction using it ----
327 // besides copies to/from Reg or spills/fills. ----
328 // Exception is done for statepoint instructions which will fold fills ----
329 // into their operands. ----
330 // We accept: ----
331 // ----
332 // %snip = COPY %Reg / FILL fi# ----
333 // %snip = USE %snip ----
334 // %snip = STATEPOINT %snip in var arg area ----
335 // %Reg = COPY %snip / SPILL %snip, fi# ----
336 // ----
337 if (!LIS.intervalIsInOneMBB(SnipLI)) 0
338 return false; 0
339 ----
340 // Number of defs should not exceed 2 not accounting defs coming from ----
341 // statepoint instructions. ----
342 unsigned NumValNums = SnipLI.getNumValNums(); 0
343 for (auto *VNI : SnipLI.vnis()) { 0
344 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
345 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT) 0
346 --NumValNums; 0
347 } ----
348 if (NumValNums > 2) 0
349 return false; 0
350 ----
351 MachineInstr *UseMI = nullptr; 0
352 ----
353 // Check that all uses satisfy our criteria. ----
354 for (MachineRegisterInfo::reg_bundle_nodbg_iterator 0
355 RI = MRI.reg_bundle_nodbg_begin(SnipLI.reg()), 0
356 E = MRI.reg_bundle_nodbg_end(); 0
357 RI != E;) { 0
358 MachineInstr &MI = *RI++; 0
359 ----
360 // Allow copies to/from Reg. ----
361 if (isCopyOfBundle(MI, Reg)) 0
362 continue; 0
363 ----
364 // Allow stack slot loads. ----
365 int FI; ----
366 if (SnipLI.reg() == TII.isLoadFromStackSlot(MI, FI) && FI == StackSlot) 0
367 continue; 0
368 ----
369 // Allow stack slot stores. ----
370 if (SnipLI.reg() == TII.isStoreToStackSlot(MI, FI) && FI == StackSlot) 0
371 continue; 0
372 ----
373 if (StatepointOpers::isFoldableReg(&MI, SnipLI.reg())) 0
374 continue; 0
375 ----
376 // Allow a single additional instruction. ----
377 if (UseMI && &MI != UseMI) 0
378 return false; 0
379 UseMI = &MI; 0
380 } ----
381 return true; 0
382 } ----
383 ----
384 /// collectRegsToSpill - Collect live range snippets that only have a single ----
385 /// real use. ----
386 void InlineSpiller::collectRegsToSpill() { 0
387 Register Reg = Edit->getReg(); 0
388 ----
389 // Main register always spills. ----
390 RegsToSpill.assign(1, Reg); 0
391 SnippetCopies.clear(); 0
392 ----
393 // Snippets all have the same original, so there can't be any for an original ----
394 // register. ----
395 if (Original == Reg) 0
396 return; 0
397 ----
398 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_bundles(Reg))) { 0
399 Register SnipReg = isCopyOfBundle(MI, Reg); 0
400 if (!isSibling(SnipReg)) 0
401 continue; 0
402 LiveInterval &SnipLI = LIS.getInterval(SnipReg); 0
403 if (!isSnippet(SnipLI)) 0
404 continue; 0
405 SnippetCopies.insert(&MI); 0
406 if (isRegToSpill(SnipReg)) 0
407 continue; 0
408 RegsToSpill.push_back(SnipReg); 0
409 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\talso spill snippet " << SnipLI << '\n'); 0
410 ++NumSnippets; 0
411 } ----
412 } ----
413 ----
414 bool InlineSpiller::isSibling(Register Reg) { 0
415 return Reg.isVirtual() && VRM.getOriginal(Reg) == Original; 0
416 } ----
417 ----
418 /// It is beneficial to spill to earlier place in the same BB in case ----
419 /// as follows: ----
420 /// There is an alternative def earlier in the same MBB. ----
421 /// Hoist the spill as far as possible in SpillMBB. This can ease ----
422 /// register pressure: ----
423 /// ----
424 /// x = def ----
425 /// y = use x ----
426 /// s = copy x ----
427 /// ----
428 /// Hoisting the spill of s to immediately after the def removes the ----
429 /// interference between x and y: ----
430 /// ----
431 /// x = def ----
432 /// spill x ----
433 /// y = use killed x ----
434 /// ----
435 /// This hoist only helps when the copy kills its source. ----
436 /// ----
437 bool InlineSpiller::hoistSpillInsideBB(LiveInterval &SpillLI, 0
438 MachineInstr &CopyMI) { ----
439 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(CopyMI); 0
440 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
441 VNInfo *VNI = SpillLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx.getRegSlot()); 0
442 assert(VNI && VNI->def == Idx.getRegSlot() && "Not defined by copy"); 0
443 #endif ----
444 ----
445 Register SrcReg = CopyMI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
446 LiveInterval &SrcLI = LIS.getInterval(SrcReg); 0
447 VNInfo *SrcVNI = SrcLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
448 LiveQueryResult SrcQ = SrcLI.Query(Idx); 0
449 MachineBasicBlock *DefMBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(SrcVNI->def); 0
450 if (DefMBB != CopyMI.getParent() || !SrcQ.isKill()) 0
451 return false; 0
452 ----
453 // Conservatively extend the stack slot range to the range of the original ----
454 // value. We may be able to do better with stack slot coloring by being more ----
455 // careful here. ----
456 assert(StackInt && "No stack slot assigned yet."); 0
457 LiveInterval &OrigLI = LIS.getInterval(Original); 0
458 VNInfo *OrigVNI = OrigLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
459 StackInt->MergeValueInAsValue(OrigLI, OrigVNI, StackInt->getValNumInfo(0)); 0
460 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tmerged orig valno " << OrigVNI->id << ": " 0
461 << *StackInt << '\n'); ----
462 ----
463 // We are going to spill SrcVNI immediately after its def, so clear out ----
464 // any later spills of the same value. ----
465 eliminateRedundantSpills(SrcLI, SrcVNI); 0
466 ----
467 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(SrcVNI->def); 0
468 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MII; 0
469 if (SrcVNI->isPHIDef()) 0
470 MII = MBB->SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug(MBB->begin()); 0
471 else { ----
472 MachineInstr *DefMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(SrcVNI->def); 0
473 assert(DefMI && "Defining instruction disappeared"); 0
474 MII = DefMI; 0
475 ++MII; 0
476 } ----
477 MachineInstrSpan MIS(MII, MBB); 0
478 // Insert spill without kill flag immediately after def. ----
479 TII.storeRegToStackSlot(*MBB, MII, SrcReg, false, StackSlot, 0
480 MRI.getRegClass(SrcReg), &TRI, Register()); 0
481 LIS.InsertMachineInstrRangeInMaps(MIS.begin(), MII); 0
482 for (const MachineInstr &MI : make_range(MIS.begin(), MII)) 0
483 getVDefInterval(MI, LIS); 0
484 --MII; // Point to store instruction. 0
485 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\thoisted: " << SrcVNI->def << '\t' << *MII); 0
486 ----
487 // If there is only 1 store instruction is required for spill, add it ----
488 // to mergeable list. In X86 AMX, 2 intructions are required to store. ----
489 // We disable the merge for this case. ----
490 if (MIS.begin() == MII) 0
491 HSpiller.addToMergeableSpills(*MII, StackSlot, Original); 0
492 ++NumSpills; 0
493 return true; 0
494 } ----
495 ----
496 /// eliminateRedundantSpills - SLI:VNI is known to be on the stack. Remove any ----
497 /// redundant spills of this value in SLI.reg and sibling copies. ----
498 void InlineSpiller::eliminateRedundantSpills(LiveInterval &SLI, VNInfo *VNI) { 0
499 assert(VNI && "Missing value"); 0
500 SmallVector, 8> WorkList; 0
501 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(&SLI, VNI)); 0
502 assert(StackInt && "No stack slot assigned yet."); 0
503 ----
504 do { ----
505 LiveInterval *LI; ----
506 std::tie(LI, VNI) = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
507 Register Reg = LI->reg(); 0
508 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Checking redundant spills for " << VNI->id << '@' 0
509 << VNI->def << " in " << *LI << '\n'); ----
510 ----
511 // Regs to spill are taken care of. ----
512 if (isRegToSpill(Reg)) 0
513 continue; 0
514 ----
515 // Add all of VNI's live range to StackInt. ----
516 StackInt->MergeValueInAsValue(*LI, VNI, StackInt->getValNumInfo(0)); 0
517 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Merged to stack int: " << *StackInt << '\n'); 0
518 ----
519 // Find all spills and copies of VNI. ----
520 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
521 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.use_nodbg_bundles(Reg))) { 0
522 if (!MI.isCopy() && !MI.mayStore()) 0
523 continue; 0
524 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(MI); 0
525 if (LI->getVNInfoAt(Idx) != VNI) 0
526 continue; 0
527 ----
528 // Follow sibling copies down the dominator tree. ----
529 if (Register DstReg = isCopyOfBundle(MI, Reg)) { 0
530 if (isSibling(DstReg)) { 0
531 LiveInterval &DstLI = LIS.getInterval(DstReg); 0
532 VNInfo *DstVNI = DstLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx.getRegSlot()); 0
533 assert(DstVNI && "Missing defined value"); 0
534 assert(DstVNI->def == Idx.getRegSlot() && "Wrong copy def slot"); 0
535 ----
536 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(&DstLI, DstVNI)); 0
537 } ----
538 continue; 0
539 } 0
540 ----
541 // Erase spills. ----
542 int FI; ----
543 if (Reg == TII.isStoreToStackSlot(MI, FI) && FI == StackSlot) { 0
544 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Redundant spill " << Idx << '\t' << MI); 0
545 // eliminateDeadDefs won't normally remove stores, so switch opcode. ----
546 MI.setDesc(TII.get(TargetOpcode::KILL)); 0
547 DeadDefs.push_back(&MI); 0
548 ++NumSpillsRemoved; 0
549 if (HSpiller.rmFromMergeableSpills(MI, StackSlot)) 0
550 --NumSpills; 0
551 } ----
552 } ----
553 } while (!WorkList.empty()); 0
554 } 0

557 // Rematerialization ----
558 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
559 ----
560 /// markValueUsed - Remember that VNI failed to rematerialize, so its defining ----
561 /// instruction cannot be eliminated. See through snippet copies ----
562 void InlineSpiller::markValueUsed(LiveInterval *LI, VNInfo *VNI) { 0
563 SmallVector, 8> WorkList; 0
564 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(LI, VNI)); 0
565 do { ----
566 std::tie(LI, VNI) = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
567 if (!UsedValues.insert(VNI).second) 0
568 continue; 0
569 ----
570 if (VNI->isPHIDef()) { 0
571 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
572 for (MachineBasicBlock *P : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
573 VNInfo *PVNI = LI->getVNInfoBefore(LIS.getMBBEndIdx(P)); 0
574 if (PVNI) 0
575 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(LI, PVNI)); 0
576 } ----
577 continue; 0
578 } 0
579 ----
580 // Follow snippet copies. ----
581 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
582 if (!SnippetCopies.count(MI)) 0
583 continue; 0
584 LiveInterval &SnipLI = LIS.getInterval(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
585 assert(isRegToSpill(SnipLI.reg()) && "Unexpected register in copy"); 0
586 VNInfo *SnipVNI = SnipLI.getVNInfoAt(VNI->def.getRegSlot(true)); 0
587 assert(SnipVNI && "Snippet undefined before copy"); 0
588 WorkList.push_back(std::make_pair(&SnipLI, SnipVNI)); 0
589 } while (!WorkList.empty()); 0
590 } 0
591 ----
592 bool InlineSpiller::canGuaranteeAssignmentAfterRemat(Register VReg, 0
593 MachineInstr &MI) { ----
594 if (!RestrictStatepointRemat) 0
595 return true; 0
596 // Here's a quick explanation of the problem we're trying to handle here: ----
597 // * There are some pseudo instructions with more vreg uses than there are ----
598 // physical registers on the machine. ----
599 // * This is normally handled by spilling the vreg, and folding the reload ----
600 // into the user instruction. (Thus decreasing the number of used vregs ----
601 // until the remainder can be assigned to physregs.) ----
602 // * However, since we may try to spill vregs in any order, we can end up ----
603 // trying to spill each operand to the instruction, and then rematting it ----
604 // instead. When that happens, the new live intervals (for the remats) are ----
605 // expected to be trivially assignable (i.e. RS_Done). However, since we ----
606 // may have more remats than physregs, we're guaranteed to fail to assign ----
607 // one. ----
608 // At the moment, we only handle this for STATEPOINTs since they're the only ----
609 // pseudo op where we've seen this. If we start seeing other instructions ----
610 // with the same problem, we need to revisit this. ----
611 if (MI.getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT) 0
612 return true; 0
613 // For STATEPOINTs we allow re-materialization for fixed arguments only hoping ----
614 // that number of physical registers is enough to cover all fixed arguments. ----
615 // If it is not true we need to revisit it. ----
616 for (unsigned Idx = StatepointOpers(&MI).getVarIdx(), 0
617 EndIdx = MI.getNumOperands(); 0
618 Idx < EndIdx; ++Idx) { 0
619 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(Idx); 0
620 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() == VReg) 0
621 return false; 0
622 } ----
623 return true; 0
624 } ----
625 ----
626 /// reMaterializeFor - Attempt to rematerialize before MI instead of reloading. ----
627 bool InlineSpiller::reMaterializeFor(LiveInterval &VirtReg, MachineInstr &MI) { 0
628 // Analyze instruction ----
629 SmallVector, 8> Ops; 0
630 VirtRegInfo RI = AnalyzeVirtRegInBundle(MI, VirtReg.reg(), &Ops); 0
631 ----
632 if (!RI.Reads) 0
633 return false; 0
634 ----
635 SlotIndex UseIdx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(MI).getRegSlot(true); 0
636 VNInfo *ParentVNI = VirtReg.getVNInfoAt(UseIdx.getBaseIndex()); 0
637 ----
638 if (!ParentVNI) { 0
639 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tadding flags: "); 0
640 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) 0
641 if (MO.getReg() == VirtReg.reg()) 0
642 MO.setIsUndef(); 0
643 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << UseIdx << '\t' << MI); 0
644 return true; 0
645 } ----
646 ----
647 if (SnippetCopies.count(&MI)) 0
648 return false; 0
649 ----
650 LiveInterval &OrigLI = LIS.getInterval(Original); 0
651 VNInfo *OrigVNI = OrigLI.getVNInfoAt(UseIdx); 0
652 LiveRangeEdit::Remat RM(ParentVNI); 0
653 RM.OrigMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(OrigVNI->def); 0
654 ----
655 if (!Edit->canRematerializeAt(RM, OrigVNI, UseIdx, false)) { 0
656 markValueUsed(&VirtReg, ParentVNI); 0
657 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tcannot remat for " << UseIdx << '\t' << MI); 0
658 return false; 0
659 } ----
660 ----
661 // If the instruction also writes VirtReg.reg, it had better not require the ----
662 // same register for uses and defs. ----
663 if (RI.Tied) { 0
664 markValueUsed(&VirtReg, ParentVNI); 0
665 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tcannot remat tied reg: " << UseIdx << '\t' << MI); 0
666 return false; 0
667 } ----
668 ----
669 // Before rematerializing into a register for a single instruction, try to ----
670 // fold a load into the instruction. That avoids allocating a new register. ----
671 if (RM.OrigMI->canFoldAsLoad() && 0
672 foldMemoryOperand(Ops, RM.OrigMI)) { 0
673 Edit->markRematerialized(RM.ParentVNI); 0
674 ++NumFoldedLoads; 0
675 return true; 0
676 } ----
677 ----
678 // If we can't guarantee that we'll be able to actually assign the new vreg, ----
679 // we can't remat. ----
680 if (!canGuaranteeAssignmentAfterRemat(VirtReg.reg(), MI)) { 0
681 markValueUsed(&VirtReg, ParentVNI); 0
682 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tcannot remat for " << UseIdx << '\t' << MI); 0
683 return false; 0
684 } ----
685 ----
686 // Allocate a new register for the remat. ----
687 Register NewVReg = Edit->createFrom(Original); 0
688 ----
689 // Finally we can rematerialize OrigMI before MI. ----
690 SlotIndex DefIdx = ----
691 Edit->rematerializeAt(*MI.getParent(), MI, NewVReg, RM, TRI); 0
692 ----
693 // We take the DebugLoc from MI, since OrigMI may be attributed to a ----
694 // different source location. ----
695 auto *NewMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(DefIdx); 0
696 NewMI->setDebugLoc(MI.getDebugLoc()); 0
697 ----
698 (void)DefIdx; ----
699 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tremat: " << DefIdx << '\t' 0
700 << *LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(DefIdx)); ----
701 ----
702 // Replace operands ----
703 for (const auto &OpPair : Ops) { 0
704 MachineOperand &MO = OpPair.first->getOperand(OpPair.second); 0
705 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isUse() && MO.getReg() == VirtReg.reg()) { 0
706 MO.setReg(NewVReg); 0
707 MO.setIsKill(); 0
708 } ----
709 } ----
710 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t " << UseIdx << '\t' << MI << '\n'); 0
711 ----
712 ++NumRemats; 0
713 return true; 0
714 } 0
715 ----
716 /// reMaterializeAll - Try to rematerialize as many uses as possible, ----
717 /// and trim the live ranges after. ----
718 void InlineSpiller::reMaterializeAll() { 0
719 if (!Edit->anyRematerializable()) 0
720 return; 0
721 ----
722 UsedValues.clear(); 0
723 ----
724 // Try to remat before all uses of snippets. ----
725 bool anyRemat = false; 0
726 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) { 0
727 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Reg); 0
728 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_bundles(Reg))) { 0
729 // Debug values are not allowed to affect codegen. ----
730 if (MI.isDebugValue()) 0
731 continue; 0
732 ----
733 assert(!MI.isDebugInstr() && "Did not expect to find a use in debug " 0
734 "instruction that isn't a DBG_VALUE"); ----
735 ----
736 anyRemat |= reMaterializeFor(LI, MI); 0
737 } ----
738 } ----
739 if (!anyRemat) 0
740 return; 0
741 ----
742 // Remove any values that were completely rematted. ----
743 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) { 0
744 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(Reg); 0
745 for (VNInfo *VNI : LI.vnis()) { 0
746 if (VNI->isUnused() || VNI->isPHIDef() || UsedValues.count(VNI)) 0
747 continue; 0
748 MachineInstr *MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(VNI->def); 0
749 MI->addRegisterDead(Reg, &TRI); 0
750 if (!MI->allDefsAreDead()) 0
751 continue; 0
752 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "All defs dead: " << *MI); 0
753 DeadDefs.push_back(MI); 0
754 } ----
755 } ----
756 ----
757 // Eliminate dead code after remat. Note that some snippet copies may be ----
758 // deleted here. ----
759 if (DeadDefs.empty()) 0
760 return; 0
761 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Remat created " << DeadDefs.size() << " dead defs.\n"); 0
762 Edit->eliminateDeadDefs(DeadDefs, RegsToSpill); 0
763 ----
764 // LiveRangeEdit::eliminateDeadDef is used to remove dead define instructions ----
765 // after rematerialization. To remove a VNI for a vreg from its LiveInterval, ----
766 // LiveIntervals::removeVRegDefAt is used. However, after non-PHI VNIs are all ----
767 // removed, PHI VNI are still left in the LiveInterval. ----
768 // So to get rid of unused reg, we need to check whether it has non-dbg ----
769 // reference instead of whether it has non-empty interval. ----
770 unsigned ResultPos = 0; 0
771 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) { 0
772 if (MRI.reg_nodbg_empty(Reg)) { 0
773 Edit->eraseVirtReg(Reg); 0
774 continue; 0
775 } ----
776 ----
777 assert(LIS.hasInterval(Reg) && 0
778 (!LIS.getInterval(Reg).empty() || !MRI.reg_nodbg_empty(Reg)) && ----
779 "Empty and not used live-range?!"); ----
780 ----
781 RegsToSpill[ResultPos++] = Reg; 0
782 } ----
783 RegsToSpill.erase(RegsToSpill.begin() + ResultPos, RegsToSpill.end()); 0
784 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << RegsToSpill.size() 0
785 << " registers to spill after remat.\n"); ----
786 } ----
787 ----
788 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
789 // Spilling ----
790 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
791 ----
792 /// If MI is a load or store of StackSlot, it can be removed. ----
793 bool InlineSpiller::coalesceStackAccess(MachineInstr *MI, Register Reg) { 0
794 int FI = 0; 0
795 Register InstrReg = TII.isLoadFromStackSlot(*MI, FI); 0
796 bool IsLoad = InstrReg; 0
797 if (!IsLoad) 0
798 InstrReg = TII.isStoreToStackSlot(*MI, FI); 0
799 ----
800 // We have a stack access. Is it the right register and slot? ----
801 if (InstrReg != Reg || FI != StackSlot) 0
802 return false; 0
803 ----
804 if (!IsLoad) 0
805 HSpiller.rmFromMergeableSpills(*MI, StackSlot); 0
806 ----
807 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Coalescing stack access: " << *MI); 0
808 LIS.RemoveMachineInstrFromMaps(*MI); 0
809 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
810 ----
811 if (IsLoad) { 0
812 ++NumReloadsRemoved; 0
813 --NumReloads; 0
814 } else { ----
815 ++NumSpillsRemoved; 0
816 --NumSpills; 0
817 } ----
818 ----
819 return true; 0
820 } ----
821 ----
822 #if !defined(NDEBUG) || defined(LLVM_ENABLE_DUMP) ----
823 LLVM_DUMP_METHOD ----
824 // Dump the range of instructions from B to E with their slot indexes. ----
825 static void dumpMachineInstrRangeWithSlotIndex(MachineBasicBlock::iterator B, 0
826 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E, ----
827 LiveIntervals const &LIS, ----
828 const char *const header, ----
829 Register VReg = Register()) { ----
830 char NextLine = '\n'; 0
831 char SlotIndent = '\t'; 0
832 ----
833 if (std::next(B) == E) { 0
834 NextLine = ' '; 0
835 SlotIndent = ' '; 0
836 } ----
837 ----
838 dbgs() << '\t' << header << ": " << NextLine; 0
839 ----
840 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = B; I != E; ++I) { 0
841 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*I).getRegSlot(); 0
842 ----
843 // If a register was passed in and this instruction has it as a ----
844 // destination that is marked as an early clobber, print the ----
845 // early-clobber slot index. ----
846 if (VReg) { 0
847 MachineOperand *MO = I->findRegisterDefOperand(VReg); 0
848 if (MO && MO->isEarlyClobber()) 0
849 Idx = Idx.getRegSlot(true); 0
850 } ----
851 ----
852 dbgs() << SlotIndent << Idx << '\t' << *I; 0
853 } ----
854 } 0
855 #endif ----
856 ----
857 /// foldMemoryOperand - Try folding stack slot references in Ops into their ----
858 /// instructions. ----
859 /// ----
860 /// @param Ops Operand indices from AnalyzeVirtRegInBundle(). ----
861 /// @param LoadMI Load instruction to use instead of stack slot when non-null. ----
862 /// @return True on success. ----
863 bool InlineSpiller:: 0
864 foldMemoryOperand(ArrayRef> Ops, ----
865 MachineInstr *LoadMI) { ----
866 if (Ops.empty()) 0
867 return false; 0
868 // Don't attempt folding in bundles. ----
869 MachineInstr *MI = Ops.front().first; 0
870 if (Ops.back().first != MI || MI->isBundled()) 0
871 return false; 0
872 ----
873 bool WasCopy = MI->isCopy(); 0
874 Register ImpReg; 0
875 ----
876 // TII::foldMemoryOperand will do what we need here for statepoint ----
877 // (fold load into use and remove corresponding def). We will replace ----
878 // uses of removed def with loads (spillAroundUses). ----
879 // For that to work we need to untie def and use to pass it through ----
880 // foldMemoryOperand and signal foldPatchpoint that it is allowed to ----
881 // fold them. ----
882 bool UntieRegs = MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT; 0
883 ----
884 // Spill subregs if the target allows it. ----
885 // We always want to spill subregs for stackmap/patchpoint pseudos. ----
886 bool SpillSubRegs = TII.isSubregFoldable() || 0
887 MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STATEPOINT || 0
888 MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT || 0
889 MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::STACKMAP; 0
890 ----
891 // TargetInstrInfo::foldMemoryOperand only expects explicit, non-tied ----
892 // operands. ----
893 SmallVector FoldOps; 0
894 for (const auto &OpPair : Ops) { 0
895 unsigned Idx = OpPair.second; 0
896 assert(MI == OpPair.first && "Instruction conflict during operand folding"); 0
897 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(Idx); 0
898 ----
899 // No point restoring an undef read, and we'll produce an invalid live ----
900 // interval. ----
901 // TODO: Is this really the correct way to handle undef tied uses? ----
902 if (MO.isUse() && !MO.readsReg() && !MO.isTied()) 0
903 continue; 0
904 ----
905 if (MO.isImplicit()) { 0
906 ImpReg = MO.getReg(); 0
907 continue; 0
908 } ----
909 ----
910 if (!SpillSubRegs && MO.getSubReg()) 0
911 return false; 0
912 // We cannot fold a load instruction into a def. ----
913 if (LoadMI && MO.isDef()) 0
914 return false; 0
915 // Tied use operands should not be passed to foldMemoryOperand. ----
916 if (UntieRegs || !MI->isRegTiedToDefOperand(Idx)) 0
917 FoldOps.push_back(Idx); 0
918 } ----
919 ----
920 // If we only have implicit uses, we won't be able to fold that. ----
921 // Moreover, TargetInstrInfo::foldMemoryOperand will assert if we try! ----
922 if (FoldOps.empty()) 0
923 return false; 0
924 ----
925 MachineInstrSpan MIS(MI, MI->getParent()); 0
926 ----
927 SmallVector > TiedOps; 0
928 if (UntieRegs) 0
929 for (unsigned Idx : FoldOps) { 0
930 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(Idx); 0
931 if (!MO.isTied()) 0
932 continue; 0
933 unsigned Tied = MI->findTiedOperandIdx(Idx); 0
934 if (MO.isUse()) 0
935 TiedOps.emplace_back(Tied, Idx); 0
936 else { ----
937 assert(MO.isDef() && "Tied to not use and def?"); 0
938 TiedOps.emplace_back(Idx, Tied); 0
939 } ----
940 MI->untieRegOperand(Idx); 0
941 } ----
942 ----
943 MachineInstr *FoldMI = ----
944 LoadMI ? TII.foldMemoryOperand(*MI, FoldOps, *LoadMI, &LIS) 0
945 : TII.foldMemoryOperand(*MI, FoldOps, StackSlot, &LIS, &VRM); 0
946 if (!FoldMI) { 0
947 // Re-tie operands. ----
948 for (auto Tied : TiedOps) 0
949 MI->tieOperands(Tied.first, Tied.second); 0
950 return false; 0
951 } ----
952 ----
953 // Remove LIS for any dead defs in the original MI not in FoldMI. ----
954 for (MIBundleOperands MO(*MI); MO.isValid(); ++MO) { 0
955 if (!MO->isReg()) 0
956 continue; 0
957 Register Reg = MO->getReg(); 0
958 if (!Reg || Reg.isVirtual() || MRI.isReserved(Reg)) { 0
959 continue; 0
960 } ----
961 // Skip non-Defs, including undef uses and internal reads. ----
962 if (MO->isUse()) 0
963 continue; 0
964 PhysRegInfo RI = AnalyzePhysRegInBundle(*FoldMI, Reg, &TRI); 0
965 if (RI.FullyDefined) 0
966 continue; 0
967 // FoldMI does not define this physreg. Remove the LI segment. ----
968 assert(MO->isDead() && "Cannot fold physreg def"); 0
969 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MI).getRegSlot(); 0
970 LIS.removePhysRegDefAt(Reg.asMCReg(), Idx); 0
971 } ----
972 ----
973 int FI; ----
974 if (TII.isStoreToStackSlot(*MI, FI) && 0
975 HSpiller.rmFromMergeableSpills(*MI, FI)) 0
976 --NumSpills; 0
977 LIS.ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(*MI, *FoldMI); 0
978 // Update the call site info. ----
979 if (MI->isCandidateForCallSiteEntry()) 0
980 MI->getMF()->moveCallSiteInfo(MI, FoldMI); 0
981 ----
982 // If we've folded a store into an instruction labelled with debug-info, ----
983 // record a substitution from the old operand to the memory operand. Handle ----
984 // the simple common case where operand 0 is the one being folded, plus when ----
985 // the destination operand is also a tied def. More values could be ----
986 // substituted / preserved with more analysis. ----
987 if (MI->peekDebugInstrNum() && Ops[0].second == 0) { 0
988 // Helper lambda. ----
989 auto MakeSubstitution = [this,FoldMI,MI,&Ops]() { 0
990 // Substitute old operand zero to the new instructions memory operand. ----
991 unsigned OldOperandNum = Ops[0].second; 0
992 unsigned NewNum = FoldMI->getDebugInstrNum(); 0
993 unsigned OldNum = MI->getDebugInstrNum(); 0
994 MF.makeDebugValueSubstitution({OldNum, OldOperandNum}, 0
995 {NewNum, MachineFunction::DebugOperandMemNumber}); ----
996 }; 0
997 ----
998 const MachineOperand &Op0 = MI->getOperand(Ops[0].second); 0
999 if (Ops.size() == 1 && Op0.isDef()) { 0
1000 MakeSubstitution(); 0
1001 } else if (Ops.size() == 2 && Op0.isDef() && MI->getOperand(1).isTied() && 0
1002 Op0.getReg() == MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) { 0
1003 MakeSubstitution(); 0
1004 } ----
1005 } else if (MI->peekDebugInstrNum()) { 0
1006 // This is a debug-labelled instruction, but the operand being folded isn't ----
1007 // at operand zero. Most likely this means it's a load being folded in. ----
1008 // Substitute any register defs from operand zero up to the one being ----
1009 // folded -- past that point, we don't know what the new operand indexes ----
1010 // will be. ----
1011 MF.substituteDebugValuesForInst(*MI, *FoldMI, Ops[0].second); 0
1012 } ----
1013 ----
1014 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1015 ----
1016 // Insert any new instructions other than FoldMI into the LIS maps. ----
1017 assert(!MIS.empty() && "Unexpected empty span of instructions!"); 0
1018 for (MachineInstr &MI : MIS) 0
1019 if (&MI != FoldMI) 0
1020 LIS.InsertMachineInstrInMaps(MI); 0
1021 ----
1022 // TII.foldMemoryOperand may have left some implicit operands on the ----
1023 // instruction. Strip them. ----
1024 if (ImpReg) 0
1025 for (unsigned i = FoldMI->getNumOperands(); i; --i) { 0
1026 MachineOperand &MO = FoldMI->getOperand(i - 1); 0
1027 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isImplicit()) 0
1028 break; 0
1029 if (MO.getReg() == ImpReg) 0
1030 FoldMI->removeOperand(i - 1); 0
1031 } ----
1032 ----
1033 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpMachineInstrRangeWithSlotIndex(MIS.begin(), MIS.end(), LIS, 0
1034 "folded")); ----
1035 ----
1036 if (!WasCopy) 0
1037 ++NumFolded; 0
1038 else if (Ops.front().second == 0) { 0
1039 ++NumSpills; 0
1040 // If there is only 1 store instruction is required for spill, add it ----
1041 // to mergeable list. In X86 AMX, 2 intructions are required to store. ----
1042 // We disable the merge for this case. ----
1043 if (std::distance(MIS.begin(), MIS.end()) <= 1) 0
1044 HSpiller.addToMergeableSpills(*FoldMI, StackSlot, Original); 0
1045 } else ----
1046 ++NumReloads; 0
1047 return true; 0
1048 } 0
1049 ----
1050 void InlineSpiller::insertReload(Register NewVReg, 0
1051 SlotIndex Idx, ----
1052 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI) { ----
1053 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1054 ----
1055 MachineInstrSpan MIS(MI, &MBB); 0
1056 TII.loadRegFromStackSlot(MBB, MI, NewVReg, StackSlot, 0
1057 MRI.getRegClass(NewVReg), &TRI, Register()); 0
1058 ----
1059 LIS.InsertMachineInstrRangeInMaps(MIS.begin(), MI); 0
1060 ----
1061 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpMachineInstrRangeWithSlotIndex(MIS.begin(), MI, LIS, "reload", 0
1062 NewVReg)); ----
1063 ++NumReloads; 0
1064 } 0
1065 ----
1066 /// Check if \p Def fully defines a VReg with an undefined value. ----
1067 /// If that's the case, that means the value of VReg is actually ----
1068 /// not relevant. ----
1069 static bool isRealSpill(const MachineInstr &Def) { 0
1070 if (!Def.isImplicitDef()) 0
1071 return true; 0
1072 assert(Def.getNumOperands() == 1 && 0
1073 "Implicit def with more than one definition"); ----
1074 // We can say that the VReg defined by Def is undef, only if it is ----
1075 // fully defined by Def. Otherwise, some of the lanes may not be ----
1076 // undef and the value of the VReg matters. ----
1077 return Def.getOperand(0).getSubReg(); 0
1078 } ----
1079 ----
1080 /// insertSpill - Insert a spill of NewVReg after MI. ----
1081 void InlineSpiller::insertSpill(Register NewVReg, bool isKill, 0
1082 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI) { ----
1083 // Spill are not terminators, so inserting spills after terminators will ----
1084 // violate invariants in MachineVerifier. ----
1085 assert(!MI->isTerminator() && "Inserting a spill after a terminator"); 0
1086 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI->getParent(); 0
1087 ----
1088 MachineInstrSpan MIS(MI, &MBB); 0
1089 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SpillBefore = std::next(MI); 0
1090 bool IsRealSpill = isRealSpill(*MI); 0
1091 ----
1092 if (IsRealSpill) 0
1093 TII.storeRegToStackSlot(MBB, SpillBefore, NewVReg, isKill, StackSlot, 0
1094 MRI.getRegClass(NewVReg), &TRI, Register()); 0
1095 else ----
1096 // Don't spill undef value. ----
1097 // Anything works for undef, in particular keeping the memory ----
1098 // uninitialized is a viable option and it saves code size and ----
1099 // run time. ----
1100 BuildMI(MBB, SpillBefore, MI->getDebugLoc(), TII.get(TargetOpcode::KILL)) 0
1101 .addReg(NewVReg, getKillRegState(isKill)); 0
1102 ----
1103 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Spill = std::next(MI); 0
1104 LIS.InsertMachineInstrRangeInMaps(Spill, MIS.end()); 0
1105 for (const MachineInstr &MI : make_range(Spill, MIS.end())) 0
1106 getVDefInterval(MI, LIS); 0
1107 ----
1108 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1109 dumpMachineInstrRangeWithSlotIndex(Spill, MIS.end(), LIS, "spill")); ----
1110 ++NumSpills; 0
1111 // If there is only 1 store instruction is required for spill, add it ----
1112 // to mergeable list. In X86 AMX, 2 intructions are required to store. ----
1113 // We disable the merge for this case. ----
1114 if (IsRealSpill && std::distance(Spill, MIS.end()) <= 1) 0
1115 HSpiller.addToMergeableSpills(*Spill, StackSlot, Original); 0
1116 } 0
1117 ----
1118 /// spillAroundUses - insert spill code around each use of Reg. ----
1119 void InlineSpiller::spillAroundUses(Register Reg) { 0
1120 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "spillAroundUses " << printReg(Reg) << '\n'); 0
1121 LiveInterval &OldLI = LIS.getInterval(Reg); 0
1122 ----
1123 // Iterate over instructions using Reg. ----
1124 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_bundles(Reg))) { 0
1125 // Debug values are not allowed to affect codegen. ----
1126 if (MI.isDebugValue()) { 0
1127 // Modify DBG_VALUE now that the value is in a spill slot. ----
1128 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
1129 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Modifying debug info due to spill:\t" << MI); 0
1130 buildDbgValueForSpill(*MBB, &MI, MI, StackSlot, Reg); 0
1131 MBB->erase(MI); 0
1132 continue; 0
1133 } 0
1134 ----
1135 assert(!MI.isDebugInstr() && "Did not expect to find a use in debug " 0
1136 "instruction that isn't a DBG_VALUE"); ----
1137 ----
1138 // Ignore copies to/from snippets. We'll delete them. ----
1139 if (SnippetCopies.count(&MI)) 0
1140 continue; 0
1141 ----
1142 // Stack slot accesses may coalesce away. ----
1143 if (coalesceStackAccess(&MI, Reg)) 0
1144 continue; 0
1145 ----
1146 // Analyze instruction. ----
1147 SmallVector, 8> Ops; 0
1148 VirtRegInfo RI = AnalyzeVirtRegInBundle(MI, Reg, &Ops); 0
1149 ----
1150 // Find the slot index where this instruction reads and writes OldLI. ----
1151 // This is usually the def slot, except for tied early clobbers. ----
1152 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(MI).getRegSlot(); 0
1153 if (VNInfo *VNI = OldLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx.getRegSlot(true))) 0
1154 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(Idx, VNI->def)) 0
1155 Idx = VNI->def; 0
1156 ----
1157 // Check for a sibling copy. ----
1158 Register SibReg = isCopyOfBundle(MI, Reg); 0
1159 if (SibReg && isSibling(SibReg)) { 0
1160 // This may actually be a copy between snippets. ----
1161 if (isRegToSpill(SibReg)) { 0
1162 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found new snippet copy: " << MI); 0
1163 SnippetCopies.insert(&MI); 0
1164 continue; 0
1165 } ----
1166 if (RI.Writes) { 0
1167 if (hoistSpillInsideBB(OldLI, MI)) { 0
1168 // This COPY is now dead, the value is already in the stack slot. ----
1169 MI.getOperand(0).setIsDead(); 0
1170 DeadDefs.push_back(&MI); 0
1171 continue; 0
1172 } ----
1173 } else { ----
1174 // This is a reload for a sib-reg copy. Drop spills downstream. ----
1175 LiveInterval &SibLI = LIS.getInterval(SibReg); 0
1176 eliminateRedundantSpills(SibLI, SibLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx)); 0
1177 // The COPY will fold to a reload below. ----
1178 } ----
1179 } ----
1180 ----
1181 // Attempt to fold memory ops. ----
1182 if (foldMemoryOperand(Ops)) 0
1183 continue; 0
1184 ----
1185 // Create a new virtual register for spill/fill. ----
1186 // FIXME: Infer regclass from instruction alone. ----
1187 Register NewVReg = Edit->createFrom(Reg); 0
1188 ----
1189 if (RI.Reads) 0
1190 insertReload(NewVReg, Idx, &MI); 0
1191 ----
1192 // Rewrite instruction operands. ----
1193 bool hasLiveDef = false; 0
1194 for (const auto &OpPair : Ops) { 0
1195 MachineOperand &MO = OpPair.first->getOperand(OpPair.second); 0
1196 MO.setReg(NewVReg); 0
1197 if (MO.isUse()) { 0
1198 if (!OpPair.first->isRegTiedToDefOperand(OpPair.second)) 0
1199 MO.setIsKill(); 0
1200 } else { ----
1201 if (!MO.isDead()) 0
1202 hasLiveDef = true; 0
1203 } ----
1204 } ----
1205 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\trewrite: " << Idx << '\t' << MI << '\n'); 0
1206 ----
1207 // FIXME: Use a second vreg if instruction has no tied ops. ----
1208 if (RI.Writes) 0
1209 if (hasLiveDef) 0
1210 insertSpill(NewVReg, true, &MI); 0
1211 } 0
1212 } 0

1214 /// spillAll - Spill all registers remaining after rematerialization. ----
1215 void InlineSpiller::spillAll() { 0
1216 // Update LiveStacks now that we are committed to spilling. ----
1217 if (StackSlot == VirtRegMap::NO_STACK_SLOT) { 0
1218 StackSlot = VRM.assignVirt2StackSlot(Original); 0
1219 StackInt = &LSS.getOrCreateInterval(StackSlot, MRI.getRegClass(Original)); 0
1220 StackInt->getNextValue(SlotIndex(), LSS.getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1221 } else ----
1222 StackInt = &LSS.getInterval(StackSlot); 0
1223 ----
1224 if (Original != Edit->getReg()) 0
1225 VRM.assignVirt2StackSlot(Edit->getReg(), StackSlot); 0
1226 ----
1227 assert(StackInt->getNumValNums() == 1 && "Bad stack interval values"); 0
1228 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) 0
1229 StackInt->MergeSegmentsInAsValue(LIS.getInterval(Reg), 0
1230 StackInt->getValNumInfo(0)); 0
1231 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Merged spilled regs: " << *StackInt << '\n'); 0
1232 ----
1233 // Spill around uses of all RegsToSpill. ----
1234 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) 0
1235 spillAroundUses(Reg); 0
1236 ----
1237 // Hoisted spills may cause dead code. ----
1238 if (!DeadDefs.empty()) { 0
1239 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Eliminating " << DeadDefs.size() << " dead defs\n"); 0
1240 Edit->eliminateDeadDefs(DeadDefs, RegsToSpill); 0
1241 } ----
1242 ----
1243 // Finally delete the SnippetCopies. ----
1244 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) { 0
1245 for (MachineInstr &MI : 0
1246 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI.reg_instructions(Reg))) { 0
1247 assert(SnippetCopies.count(&MI) && "Remaining use wasn't a snippet copy"); 0
1248 // FIXME: Do this with a LiveRangeEdit callback. ----
1249 LIS.getSlotIndexes()->removeSingleMachineInstrFromMaps(MI); 0
1250 MI.eraseFromBundle(); 0
1251 } ----
1252 } ----
1253 ----
1254 // Delete all spilled registers. ----
1255 for (Register Reg : RegsToSpill) 0
1256 Edit->eraseVirtReg(Reg); 0
1257 } 0

1265 Original = VRM.getOriginal(edit.getReg()); 0
1266 StackSlot = VRM.getStackSlot(Original); 0

1308 /// When a spill is removed, remove the spill from MergeableSpills map. ----
1309 /// Return true if the spill is removed successfully. ----
1310 bool HoistSpillHelper::rmFromMergeableSpills(MachineInstr &Spill, 0
1311 int StackSlot) { ----

1313 if (It == StackSlotToOrigLI.end()) 0
1314 return false; 0

1316 VNInfo *OrigVNI = It->second->getVNInfoAt(Idx.getRegSlot()); 0
1317 std::pair MIdx = std::make_pair(StackSlot, OrigVNI); 0
1318 return MergeableSpills[MIdx].erase(&Spill); 0
1319 } ----

1321 /// Check BB to see if it is a possible target BB to place a hoisted spill, ----
1322 /// i.e., there should be a living sibling of OrigReg at the insert point. ----
1323 bool HoistSpillHelper::isSpillCandBB(LiveInterval &OrigLI, VNInfo &OrigVNI, 0
1324 MachineBasicBlock &BB, Register &LiveReg) { ----
1325 SlotIndex Idx = IPA.getLastInsertPoint(OrigLI, BB); 0
1326 // The original def could be after the last insert point in the root block, ----
1327 // we can't hoist to here. ----
1328 if (Idx < OrigVNI.def) { 0
1329 // TODO: We could be better here. If LI is not alive in landing pad ----
1330 // we could hoist spill after LIP. ----
1331 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "can't spill in root block - def after LIP\n"); 0
1332 return false; 0
1333 } ----
1334 Register OrigReg = OrigLI.reg(); 0
1335 SmallSetVector &Siblings = Virt2SiblingsMap[OrigReg]; 0
1336 assert(OrigLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx) == &OrigVNI && "Unexpected VNI"); 0
1337 ----
1338 for (const Register &SibReg : Siblings) { 0
1339 LiveInterval &LI = LIS.getInterval(SibReg); 0
1340 VNInfo *VNI = LI.getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
1341 if (VNI) { 0
1342 LiveReg = SibReg; 0
1343 return true; 0
1344 } ----
1345 } ----
1346 return false; 0
1347 } ----

1349 /// Remove redundant spills in the same BB. Save those redundant spills in ----
1350 /// SpillsToRm, and save the spill to keep and its BB in SpillBBToSpill map. ----
1351 void HoistSpillHelper::rmRedundantSpills( 0
1352 SmallPtrSet &Spills, ----
1353 SmallVectorImpl &SpillsToRm, ----
1354 DenseMap &SpillBBToSpill) { ----
1355 // For each spill saw, check SpillBBToSpill[] and see if its BB already has ----
1356 // another spill inside. If a BB contains more than one spill, only keep the ----
1357 // earlier spill with smaller SlotIndex. ----
1358 for (auto *const CurrentSpill : Spills) { 0
1359 MachineBasicBlock *Block = CurrentSpill->getParent(); 0
1360 MachineDomTreeNode *Node = MDT.getBase().getNode(Block); 0
1361 MachineInstr *PrevSpill = SpillBBToSpill[Node]; 0
1362 if (PrevSpill) { 0
1363 SlotIndex PIdx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*PrevSpill); 0
1364 SlotIndex CIdx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*CurrentSpill); 0
1365 MachineInstr *SpillToRm = (CIdx > PIdx) ? CurrentSpill : PrevSpill; 0
1366 MachineInstr *SpillToKeep = (CIdx > PIdx) ? PrevSpill : CurrentSpill; 0
1367 SpillsToRm.push_back(SpillToRm); 0
1368 SpillBBToSpill[MDT.getBase().getNode(Block)] = SpillToKeep; 0
1369 } else { ----
1370 SpillBBToSpill[MDT.getBase().getNode(Block)] = CurrentSpill; 0
1371 } ----
1372 } ----
1373 for (auto *const SpillToRm : SpillsToRm) 0
1374 Spills.erase(SpillToRm); 0
1375 } 0
1376 ----
1377 /// Starting from \p Root find a top-down traversal order of the dominator ----
1378 /// tree to visit all basic blocks containing the elements of \p Spills. ----
1379 /// Redundant spills will be found and put into \p SpillsToRm at the same ----
1380 /// time. \p SpillBBToSpill will be populated as part of the process and ----
1381 /// maps a basic block to the first store occurring in the basic block. ----
1382 /// \post SpillsToRm.union(Spills\@post) == Spills\@pre ----
1383 void HoistSpillHelper::getVisitOrders( 0
1384 MachineBasicBlock *Root, SmallPtrSet &Spills, ----
1385 SmallVectorImpl &Orders, ----
1386 SmallVectorImpl &SpillsToRm, ----
1387 DenseMap &SpillsToKeep, ----
1388 DenseMap &SpillBBToSpill) { ----
1389 // The set contains all the possible BB nodes to which we may hoist ----
1390 // original spills. ----
1391 SmallPtrSet WorkSet; 0
1392 // Save the BB nodes on the path from the first BB node containing ----
1393 // non-redundant spill to the Root node. ----
1394 SmallPtrSet NodesOnPath; 0
1395 // All the spills to be hoisted must originate from a single def instruction ----
1396 // to the OrigReg. It means the def instruction should dominate all the spills ----
1397 // to be hoisted. We choose the BB where the def instruction is located as ----
1398 // the Root. ----
1399 MachineDomTreeNode *RootIDomNode = MDT[Root]->getIDom(); 0
1400 // For every node on the dominator tree with spill, walk up on the dominator ----
1401 // tree towards the Root node until it is reached. If there is other node ----
1402 // containing spill in the middle of the path, the previous spill saw will ----
1403 // be redundant and the node containing it will be removed. All the nodes on ----
1404 // the path starting from the first node with non-redundant spill to the Root ----
1405 // node will be added to the WorkSet, which will contain all the possible ----
1406 // locations where spills may be hoisted to after the loop below is done. ----
1407 for (auto *const Spill : Spills) { 0
1408 MachineBasicBlock *Block = Spill->getParent(); 0
1409 MachineDomTreeNode *Node = MDT[Block]; 0
1410 MachineInstr *SpillToRm = nullptr; 0
1411 while (Node != RootIDomNode) { 0
1412 // If Node dominates Block, and it already contains a spill, the spill in ----
1413 // Block will be redundant. ----
1414 if (Node != MDT[Block] && SpillBBToSpill[Node]) { 0
1415 SpillToRm = SpillBBToSpill[MDT[Block]]; 0
1416 break; 0
1417 /// If we see the Node already in WorkSet, the path from the Node to ----
1418 /// the Root node must already be traversed by another spill. ----
1419 /// Then no need to repeat. ----
1420 } else if (WorkSet.count(Node)) { 0
1421 break; 0
1422 } else { ----
1423 NodesOnPath.insert(Node); 0
1424 } ----
1425 Node = Node->getIDom(); 0
1426 } ----
1427 if (SpillToRm) { 0
1428 SpillsToRm.push_back(SpillToRm); 0
1429 } else { ----
1430 // Add a BB containing the original spills to SpillsToKeep -- i.e., ----
1431 // set the initial status before hoisting start. The value of BBs ----
1432 // containing original spills is set to 0, in order to descriminate ----
1433 // with BBs containing hoisted spills which will be inserted to ----
1434 // SpillsToKeep later during hoisting. ----
1435 SpillsToKeep[MDT[Block]] = 0; 0
1436 WorkSet.insert(NodesOnPath.begin(), NodesOnPath.end()); 0
1437 } ----
1438 NodesOnPath.clear(); 0
1439 } ----
1440 ----
1441 // Sort the nodes in WorkSet in top-down order and save the nodes ----
1442 // in Orders. Orders will be used for hoisting in runHoistSpills. ----
1443 unsigned idx = 0; 0
1444 Orders.push_back(MDT.getBase().getNode(Root)); 0
1445 do { ----
1446 MachineDomTreeNode *Node = Orders[idx++]; 0
1447 for (MachineDomTreeNode *Child : Node->children()) { 0
1448 if (WorkSet.count(Child)) 0
1449 Orders.push_back(Child); 0
1450 } ----
1451 } while (idx != Orders.size()); 0
1452 assert(Orders.size() == WorkSet.size() && 0
1453 "Orders have different size with WorkSet"); ----
1454 ----
1455 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1456 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Orders size is " << Orders.size() << "\n"); 0
1457 SmallVector::reverse_iterator RIt = Orders.rbegin(); 0
1458 for (; RIt != Orders.rend(); RIt++) 0
1459 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "BB" << (*RIt)->getBlock()->getNumber() << ","); 0
1460 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
1461 #endif ----
1462 } 0
1463 ----
1464 /// Try to hoist spills according to BB hotness. The spills to removed will ----
1465 /// be saved in \p SpillsToRm. The spills to be inserted will be saved in ----
1466 /// \p SpillsToIns. ----
1467 void HoistSpillHelper::runHoistSpills( 0
1468 LiveInterval &OrigLI, VNInfo &OrigVNI, ----
1469 SmallPtrSet &Spills, ----
1470 SmallVectorImpl &SpillsToRm, ----
1471 DenseMap &SpillsToIns) { ----
1472 // Visit order of dominator tree nodes. ----
1473 SmallVector Orders; 0
1474 // SpillsToKeep contains all the nodes where spills are to be inserted ----
1475 // during hoisting. If the spill to be inserted is an original spill ----
1476 // (not a hoisted one), the value of the map entry is 0. If the spill ----
1477 // is a hoisted spill, the value of the map entry is the VReg to be used ----
1478 // as the source of the spill. ----
1479 DenseMap SpillsToKeep; 0
1480 // Map from BB to the first spill inside of it. ----
1481 DenseMap SpillBBToSpill; 0
1482 ----
1483 rmRedundantSpills(Spills, SpillsToRm, SpillBBToSpill); 0
1484 ----
1485 MachineBasicBlock *Root = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(OrigVNI.def); 0
1486 getVisitOrders(Root, Spills, Orders, SpillsToRm, SpillsToKeep, 0
1487 SpillBBToSpill); ----
1488 ----
1489 // SpillsInSubTreeMap keeps the map from a dom tree node to a pair of ----
1490 // nodes set and the cost of all the spills inside those nodes. ----
1491 // The nodes set are the locations where spills are to be inserted ----
1492 // in the subtree of current node. ----
1493 using NodesCostPair = ----
1494 std::pair, BlockFrequency>; ----
1495 DenseMap SpillsInSubTreeMap; 0
1496 ----
1497 // Iterate Orders set in reverse order, which will be a bottom-up order ----
1498 // in the dominator tree. Once we visit a dom tree node, we know its ----
1499 // children have already been visited and the spill locations in the ----
1500 // subtrees of all the children have been determined. ----
1501 SmallVector::reverse_iterator RIt = Orders.rbegin(); 0
1502 for (; RIt != Orders.rend(); RIt++) { 0
1503 MachineBasicBlock *Block = (*RIt)->getBlock(); 0
1504 ----
1505 // If Block contains an original spill, simply continue. ----
1506 if (SpillsToKeep.contains(*RIt) && !SpillsToKeep[*RIt]) { 0
1507 SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].first.insert(*RIt); 0
1508 // SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].second contains the cost of spill. ----
1509 SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].second = MBFI.getBlockFreq(Block); 0
1510 continue; 0
1511 } ----
1512 ----
1513 // Collect spills in subtree of current node (*RIt) to ----
1514 // SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].first. ----
1515 for (MachineDomTreeNode *Child : (*RIt)->children()) { 0
1516 if (!SpillsInSubTreeMap.contains(Child)) 0
1517 continue; 0
1518 // The stmt "SpillsInSubTree = SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].first" below ----
1519 // should be placed before getting the begin and end iterators of ----
1520 // SpillsInSubTreeMap[Child].first, or else the iterators may be ----
1521 // invalidated when SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt] is seen the first time ----
1522 // and the map grows and then the original buckets in the map are moved. ----
1523 SmallPtrSet &SpillsInSubTree = ----
1524 SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].first; 0
1525 BlockFrequency &SubTreeCost = SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].second; 0
1526 SubTreeCost += SpillsInSubTreeMap[Child].second; 0
1527 auto BI = SpillsInSubTreeMap[Child].first.begin(); 0
1528 auto EI = SpillsInSubTreeMap[Child].first.end(); 0
1529 SpillsInSubTree.insert(BI, EI); 0
1530 SpillsInSubTreeMap.erase(Child); 0
1531 } ----
1532 ----
1533 SmallPtrSet &SpillsInSubTree = ----
1534 SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].first; 0
1535 BlockFrequency &SubTreeCost = SpillsInSubTreeMap[*RIt].second; 0
1536 // No spills in subtree, simply continue. ----
1537 if (SpillsInSubTree.empty()) 0
1538 continue; 0
1539 ----
1540 // Check whether Block is a possible candidate to insert spill. ----
1541 Register LiveReg; 0
1542 if (!isSpillCandBB(OrigLI, OrigVNI, *Block, LiveReg)) 0
1543 continue; 0
1544 ----
1545 // If there are multiple spills that could be merged, bias a little ----
1546 // to hoist the spill. ----
1547 BranchProbability MarginProb = (SpillsInSubTree.size() > 1) 0
1548 ? BranchProbability(9, 10) ----
1549 : BranchProbability(1, 1); 0
1550 if (SubTreeCost > MBFI.getBlockFreq(Block) * MarginProb) { 0
1551 // Hoist: Move spills to current Block. ----
1552 for (auto *const SpillBB : SpillsInSubTree) { 0
1553 // When SpillBB is a BB contains original spill, insert the spill ----
1554 // to SpillsToRm. ----
1555 if (SpillsToKeep.contains(SpillBB) && !SpillsToKeep[SpillBB]) { 0
1556 MachineInstr *SpillToRm = SpillBBToSpill[SpillBB]; 0
1557 SpillsToRm.push_back(SpillToRm); 0
1558 } ----
1559 // SpillBB will not contain spill anymore, remove it from SpillsToKeep. ----
1560 SpillsToKeep.erase(SpillBB); 0
1561 } ----
1562 // Current Block is the BB containing the new hoisted spill. Add it to ----
1563 // SpillsToKeep. LiveReg is the source of the new spill. ----
1564 SpillsToKeep[*RIt] = LiveReg; 0
1565 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1566 dbgs() << "spills in BB: "; ----
1567 for (const auto Rspill : SpillsInSubTree) ----
1568 dbgs() << Rspill->getBlock()->getNumber() << " "; ----
1569 dbgs() << "were promoted to BB" << (*RIt)->getBlock()->getNumber() ----
1570 << "\n"; ----
1571 }); ----
1572 SpillsInSubTree.clear(); 0
1573 SpillsInSubTree.insert(*RIt); 0
1574 SubTreeCost = MBFI.getBlockFreq(Block); 0
1575 } ----
1576 } ----
1577 // For spills in SpillsToKeep with LiveReg set (i.e., not original spill), ----
1578 // save them to SpillsToIns. ----
1579 for (const auto &Ent : SpillsToKeep) { 0
1580 if (Ent.second) 0
1581 SpillsToIns[Ent.first->getBlock()] = Ent.second; 0
1582 } ----
1583 } 0
1584 ----
1585 /// For spills with equal values, remove redundant spills and hoist those left ----
1586 /// to less hot spots. ----
1587 /// ----
1588 /// Spills with equal values will be collected into the same set in ----
1589 /// MergeableSpills when spill is inserted. These equal spills are originated ----
1590 /// from the same defining instruction and are dominated by the instruction. ----
1591 /// Before hoisting all the equal spills, redundant spills inside in the same ----
1592 /// BB are first marked to be deleted. Then starting from the spills left, walk ----
1593 /// up on the dominator tree towards the Root node where the define instruction ----
1594 /// is located, mark the dominated spills to be deleted along the way and ----
1595 /// collect the BB nodes on the path from non-dominated spills to the define ----
1596 /// instruction into a WorkSet. The nodes in WorkSet are the candidate places ----
1597 /// where we are considering to hoist the spills. We iterate the WorkSet in ----
1598 /// bottom-up order, and for each node, we will decide whether to hoist spills ----
1599 /// inside its subtree to that node. In this way, we can get benefit locally ----
1600 /// even if hoisting all the equal spills to one cold place is impossible. ----
1601 void HoistSpillHelper::hoistAllSpills() { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1602 SmallVector NewVRegs; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1603 LiveRangeEdit Edit(nullptr, NewVRegs, MF, LIS, &VRM, this); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1604 ----
1605 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MRI.getNumVirtRegs(); i != e; ++i) { 18 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1606 Register Reg = Register::index2VirtReg(i); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1607 Register Original = VRM.getPreSplitReg(Reg); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1608 if (!MRI.def_empty(Reg)) 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1609 Virt2SiblingsMap[Original].insert(Reg); 16 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1610 } ----
1611 ----
1612 // Each entry in MergeableSpills contains a spill set with equal values. ----
1613 for (auto &Ent : MergeableSpills) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1614 int Slot = Ent.first.first; 0
1615 LiveInterval &OrigLI = *StackSlotToOrigLI[Slot]; 0
1616 VNInfo *OrigVNI = Ent.first.second; 0
1617 SmallPtrSet &EqValSpills = Ent.second; 0
1618 if (Ent.second.empty()) 0
1619 continue; 0
1620 ----
1621 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1622 dbgs() << "\nFor Slot" << Slot << " and VN" << OrigVNI->id << ":\n" ----
1623 << "Equal spills in BB: "; ----
1624 for (const auto spill : EqValSpills) ----
1625 dbgs() << spill->getParent()->getNumber() << " "; ----
